{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idca3699f7-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1467a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1467a"},"text":"§ 1467a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Working capital fund; credit card refunds or rebates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Refunds or rebates received on an on-going basis from a credit card services provider under the Department of the Interior’s charge card programs, on and after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-11"},"text":"October 11, 2000","children":[],"tail":", may be deposited to and retained without fiscal year limitation in the Departmental Working Capital Fund established under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1467"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1467","children":[],"tail":" and used to fund management initiatives of general benefit to the Department of the Interior’s bureaus and offices as determined by the Secretary or his designee."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idca3699f8-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/291/tI/s113"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–291, title I, § 113","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/943"},"text":"114 Stat. 943","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idca3699f9-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idca3699fa-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions